months ago","text":"Me and my friends booked in for a roast this afternoon which we were really looking forward to at the new LGBT+ venue. We had our booking for 15:00 however we were waiting outside for around 10 minutes without anyone signposting when we'd get seen to. When we were seated, the service was quick for drinks and food orders but we were waiting for our food for a good 40-50 minutes. We could only order roasts from the menu and when we received our orders all of us were pretty underwhelmed. I can appreciate it's super busy and a new venue but we were really disappointed with our roasts, especially priced at £18 which is quite expensive for a roast in Clapham and didn't eat them unfortunately; my chicken was very dry, the potatoes and veggies were cold and we were missing parsnips from our plates. The gravy we received wasn't gravy. It was literally a sort of oil and it wasn't very pleasant to taste. We asked for condiments and parsnips which were never received, the gravy was still not up to standard for £18 and my friends potatoes were the same potatoes she had originally and were not heated up properly. As we were not happy or eat the roasts we were not charged for our meals. We were charged for our drinks which is fair however we were still charged a service charge which I didn't quite understand as our overall experience was definitely not up to scratch as we left disappointed and ended up going to the Clapham North for our roasts which was amazing and cheaper. I completely understand this is a new venue but the food overall wasn't great, except for the cauliflower cheese, I feel the roast is seriously overpriced and there was slight confusion amongst the staff in terms of what was going on meaning our issues I feel were not completely addressed accordingly. I think with a few adjustments with the food, a review on food prices and training for staff, I can see the venue being amazing because the vibe was great but overall, I can definitely find a better roast in Clapham for cheaper and without any issues.","time":1607343807},{"author_name":"Daniel Hall","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100302506711841603380/reviews","language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjrWWejyhJ5CNtf4C9L4oiuQBMmf1xvZnL17GpV4eg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"We had such a lovely evening; great food, atmosphere and our server Jamie was so welcoming and friendly. The ingredients were of very good quality, the meat in particular. I have to say that I found the cooking a touch bland, they needed to season everything quite a bit more. My partner and I found the starter and main needed more salt to it. The gravy was a touch too weak and watery. They provide complimentary Yorkshire puddings which is a great touch but they were a little too dry. The same with the Yorkshire with the main roast, which needed more gravy. Satisfyingly there is a large serving of the trimmings, you will not be needing anymore. The drinks are very good, I started with a good punchy Bloody Mary and then moved onto a good red wine. All very well priced too. Pick your poison with ease, this fine establishment serves a plethora of beer, cider and ales, the quality is high and it comes as you’d like it, cold, wet and in a glass.
